🔹 INNER JOIN vs LEFT JOIN
INNER JOIN → “Gives only the common records between two tables.”
SELECT e.name, d.department_name
FROM employee e
INNER JOIN department d ON e.department_id = d.id;

LEFT JOIN → “Gives all records from the left table, and matching ones from the right. If no match, NULL is shown.”
SELECT e.name, d.department_name
FROM employee e
LEFT JOIN department d ON e.department_id = d.id;
